WORLD IN BRIEF; 
CHINA; 
NUCLEAR BOMB TEST 1ST IN NEARLY 2 YEARS 
China conducted its first nuclear weapon test in nearly two years, monitors in 
Sweden said. Scientists at the Hagfors Observatory said seismic signals picked 
up over the weekend indicated that a bomb with a yield of 40 to 50 kilotons was 
detonated at the Lop Nor test site in northwestern China. 
